cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper deals with the automatic detection of pathological voice based on computerized analysis of acoustic signals, which falls under the domain of speech processing and analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms such as gradient boosting and deep learning, which are commonly used in natural language processing and computer vision, indicating that the paper could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of anomaly detection, which is a subfield of machine learning, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
